org.openbel.framework.api
Class KamSpecies

java.lang.Object
  org.openbel.framework.api.KamSpecies
All Implemented Interfaces:
Kam, KamStoreObject
public class KamSpecies
extends Object
implements Kam

KamSpecies defines a kam that provides a species-specific view using a species dialect. The KamSpecies orthologization occurs on construction in KamSpecies(Kam, SpeciesDialect, KamStore). The existing Kam is cloned to preserve the original Kam. The process of Kam orthologization involves:

  1. Removing orthologous edges.
  2. Redirecting (remove/create) ortholog's edges to the species node being collapsed to.
  3. Remove ortholog nodes. This is done at construction of KamSpecies.

Author:
Anthony Bargnesi <abargnesi@selventa.com>
See Also:

collapseNode

public void collapseNode(Kam.KamNode from,
                         Kam.KamNode to)
Remove the from Kam.KamNode and collapse its adjacent network to the to Kam.KamNode. Any edges shared between from and to are necessarily deleted.

For example given: 

    A -> B -> C
         |
         V
    E <- D -> F
if we replace B with D we end up with: 
    A -> D -> C
        / \
       v   v
      E     F

Specified by:
collapseNode in interface Kam
Parameters:
from - Kam.KamNode node to collapse
to - Kam.KamNode node that is preserved and subsumes the network of from
